    {
      "type": "minecraft:plain_message",
      "contents": {
        "text": "The Logging skill is leveled up by chopping oak logs. As the level increases, the bonus drop chance per chopped log also increases."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "minecraft:plain_message",
      "contents": {
        "text": "XP is gained by:",
        "color": "dark_green"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "minecraft:plain_message",
      "contents": {
        "text": "• Chopping Oak Logs (Eichenholz)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "minecraft:plain_message",
      "contents": {
        "text": "What do you get?",
        "color": "dark_green"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "minecraft:plain_message",
      "contents": {
        "text": "As the level increases, the bonus drop chance per chopped log also increases. Higher levels unlock more drops from the Logging Bonus Loot Table.\n \nThe corresponding tool is the Element Axe:\n• Common: +50% Drop-Chance\n• Uncommon: +100%\n• Further levels increase the multiplier even more\n \nBlueprints for upgrades drop when leveling up."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "minecraft:plain_message",
      "contents": {
        "text": "Leaderboard:",
        "color": "dark_green"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "minecraft:plain_message",
      "contents": {
        "text": "In the Hub, there is a Logging Leaderboard that shows the top 5 players by Logging Level."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "minecraft:plain_message",
      "contents": {
        "text": "XP-Boost through the Catch-Up System:",
        "color": "dark_green"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "minecraft:plain_message",
      "contents": {
        "text": "Players who are far behind the server leader automatically receive more XP per action. More information in the Catch-Up System tab."
      }
    }
